Air France, Barclays, Commerzbank: European Equity Preview

-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 
2011-04-08T04:01:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/air-france-barclays-commerzbank-european-equity-preview.html
The following companies’ shares may
have unusual moves in European trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index fell 0.3 percent to 280.78. The
Stoxx 50 Index rose 0.1 percent to 2,639.36. The Euro Stoxx 50
Index, a benchmark for nations using the euro, fell 0.3 percent
to 2,963.69.  Air France-KLM (AF)  Group: The largest French airline
said it will resume direct flights to  Tokyo . The shares fell 0.1
percent to 11.63 euros.  Amec Plc (AMEC)  : AMEC Earth and Environmental, a
subsidiary of AMEC Plc, and a closely held California company
protested a $500 million Navy contract to clean hazardous sites
awarded to six companies, including units of Aecom Technology
Corp. (ACM US) and Arcadis NV (ARCAD NA). The shares fell 0.4
percent to 1,179 pence.  Barclays Plc (BARC LN): Barclays Bank SA, the U.K. lender’s
Spanish unit, said in a filing its board agreed to propose a
capital increase of as much as 600 million euros and a boost to
capital of as much as 700 million euros via buying back debt.
Barclays Bank SA will buy back subordinated debt from  Barclays
Plc (BARC) , a spokeswoman for the Spanish unit said in a telephone
interview. The shares advanced 0.2 percent to 295.25 pence.  Commerzbank AG (CBK)  : Short selling of  Germany ’s second
largest lender’s shares topped 1 billion euros ($1.43 billion)
in recent weeks, Financial Times Deutschland reported, citing
financial data service Dataexplorers Ltd. The shares fell 4.9
percent to 5.42 euros.  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  : U.S. tax authorities are
seeking authorization to go after information from HSBC Holdings
Plc that might identify account holders in  India  who evaded
taxes, the  Justice Department  said in a statement. The stock
gained 1 percent to 667.2 pence.  Lafarge (LG FP): The world’s largest cement maker has
mandated BNP Paribas and Citi to study a sale of its plaster
unit, Reuters reported, citing sources close to the matter. The
European arm of the plaster division has attracted bid interest
from private equity funds, Reuters said. The shares fell 0.3
percent to 45.11 euros.  Roularta Media Group NV (ROU)  : Belgium’s biggest
magazine publisher said its French unit bought ulike.net, a
cultural community website with 850,000 unique visitors a month,
without disclosing the terms of the transaction. Roularta
declined 0.5 percent to 24.58 euros.  Veolia Environnement SA (VIE)  : The utility signed a 2.5
billion-euro multi-currency syndicated five-year loan with a
group of 31 banks and 500 million-euro three-year loan in
eastern European currencies, both to refinance existing debt.
The shares fell 0.1 percent to 21.78 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
